article.headline: Kent St. 82, E. Michigan 46
article.story: KENT, Ohio (AP) -- Chris Singletary scored a career-high 16 points and Armon Gates hit all four of his 3-point shots in the opening half to lead Kent State past Eastern Michigan 82-46 on Saturday. Gates scored all 12 of his points in the first half as the Golden Flashes (14-8, 7-2 Mid-American Conference) rolled to a 46-19 lead. The win was Kent State's fifth in a row and sixth straight at home. Julian Sullinger and Omni Smith each scored 12 points for the Golden Flashes, while Jordan Mincy had a career-best eight assists and Haminn Quaintance had four points, six assists and nine rebounds off the bench. Devon Dumes led Eastern Michigan (8-14, 3-6) with 13 points, with Brandon Bowdry adding 12. The Eagles never led and trailed by as many as 38 points in the second half. The Golden Flashes made 56 percent of their shots from the field for the game -- double Eastern Michigan's 28-percent shooting.
